==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Usufructuary
<hw>U`su*fruc"tu*a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>usufructuarius</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A person who has
the use of property and reaps the profits of it.</def>
<rj><au>Wharton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Usufructuary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Usufructuary
<hw>U`su*fruc"tu*a*ry</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Of or
pertaining to a usufruct; having the nature of a usufruct.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The ordinary graces bequeathed by Christ to his church, as the
<qex>usufructuary</qex> property of all its members.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Usurary</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Usurarious</ent>⟦br⟧
